  <p class="eyebrow">Solo Female Travel</p>
  <h1>Specific advice. Not vague warnings.</h1>
  <p>Sri Lanka is generally safe for solo female travellers. This guide gives you the specific, actionable information that generic guides skip — sourced from the community.</p>
</div>

<!-- HONEST OVERVIEW -->
<section style="background:var(--white);">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">The honest picture</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Sri Lanka for solo women</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--muted);max-width:60ch;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Sri Lanka scores well compared to many South/Southeast Asian destinations for solo female travel. Street harassment exists but is far less aggressive than in some neighbouring countries. Violent crime against tourists is rare. The main issues are persistent attention, overcharging, and unwanted company on tuk-tuks — all very manageable with the right strategies.</p>
  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1rem;max-width:600px;">
    <div style="background:#e4f0e9;border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:1rem;">
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;color:#1a4a2e;margin-bottom:0.4rem;">✓ Generally safe</p>
      <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#2d6b3d;">Low violent crime, friendly culture, good tourist infrastructure.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#fdf2e9;border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:1rem;">
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;color:#7a4010;margin-bottom:0.4rem;">⚠ Watch for</p>
      <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#a0530f;">Persistent touts, staring in rural areas, overcharging solo travellers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRANSPORT SAFETY -->
<section style="background:var(--terra-pale);">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Getting around safely</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Transport for solo women</h2>
  <p class="section-desc">This is where specific advice matters most. Here's what the community recommends.</p>
  <div class="safety-grid">
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🛺 PickMe (top choice)</h4>
      <p>Sri Lanka's dominant ride-hailing app. Drivers are rated and registered — far safer than hailing from the street. Save the app before you arrive. Works well in Colombo, Kandy, Galle, and growing in coastal towns.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🛺 Uber (second choice)</h4>
      <p>Available in major cities. Slightly fewer drivers than PickMe but well-regulated. Share your trip with someone before you get in — both apps have a share-trip feature.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🛺 Hailing off the street</h4>
      <p>Always negotiate price before getting in. Ask your guesthouse for a typical fare first — you'll know if you're being overcharged. Say "I know the price" if they try to increase it on arrival.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🚂 Trains (generally safe)</h4>
      <p>Trains are safe. Carriages can be crowded. In the busy 2nd and 3rd class, sit near other women or families, especially on night services. The 1st class observation carriage is quieter and has more space.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🚌 Buses</h4>
      <p>Crowded buses can involve unwanted contact — intentional or not. Stand your ground or move. Women's seats at the front of CTB buses are reserved by convention, though not always enforced.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🌙 Night travel</h4>
      <p>Stick to trains for night travel — safer than night buses. If taking a bus, book semi-luxury sleeper buses rather than standard. Avoid late-night tuk-tuks in unfamiliar areas — book via app instead.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ACCOMMODATION -->
<section style="background:var(--white);">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Where to stay</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Vetted guesthouses</h2>
  <p class="section-desc">These are the criteria our community rates guesthouses on — not stars, but what actually matters for solo female travellers.</p>
  <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.75rem;max-width:700px;">
    <div style="background:var(--page);border:1px solid var(--sand);border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:1rem;display:flex;gap:0.875rem;align-items:flex-start;">
      <span style="font-size:1.4rem;flex-shrink:0;">🔐</span>
      <div>
        <p style="font-weight:600;font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">Door locks on bedrooms</p>
        <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--muted);">Sounds obvious, but some budget guesthouses have simple latches. Ask specifically about bedroom door locks when booking — a deadbolt or key lock is what you want.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--page);border:1px solid var(--sand);border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:1rem;display:flex;gap:0.875rem;align-items:flex-start;">
      <span style="font-size:1.4rem;flex-shrink:0;">💡</span>
      <div>
        <p style="font-weight:600;font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">Well-lit entrance and corridors</p>
        <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--muted);">Check satellite photos or ask previous guests (hostelworld reviews often mention this). Arriving after dark to a dark guesthouse is an avoidable stress.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--page);border:1px solid var(--sand);border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:1rem;display:flex;gap:0.875rem;align-items:flex-start;">
      <span style="font-size:1.4rem;flex-shrink:0;">👤</span>
      <div>
        <p style="font-weight:600;font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">Responsive, professional hosts</p>
        <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--muted);">Message the host before booking — response time and professionalism are good signals. Hosts who respond within an hour and answer questions directly are a good sign.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--page);border:1px solid var(--sand);border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:1rem;display:flex;gap:0.875rem;align-items:flex-start;">
      <span style="font-size:1.4rem;flex-shrink:0;">🌍</span>
      <div>
        <p style="font-weight:600;font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">Common areas with other travellers</p>
        <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--muted);">Guesthouses with shared common rooms tend to have better communities and are often safer — you're not isolated in a private room in an empty building.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- HIKING -->
<section style="background:var(--page);">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Hiking safety</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Solo hikes — the specific guide</h2>
  <p class="section-desc">Sri Lanka has incredible hiking. Here's how to do it safely solo.</p>
  <div class="safety-grid">
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🥾 Adam's Peak (Sri Pada)</h4>
      <p>The pilgrimage season (Dec–May) is actually the safest time — thousands of pilgrims on the path all night. Solo women regularly do this hike. Start at 02:00–03:00 for sunrise. Well-lit path. Avoid off-season (June–Nov) when the path is deserted.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🥾 Ella Rock</h4>
      <p>Poorly marked trail — getting lost is common. Go with at least one other person or hire a guide (LKR 1,000–2,000, easily arranged in Ella). Morning starts are best; the trail can be deserted by afternoon.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🥾 Knuckles Range</h4>
      <p>Multi-day hiking. Do not attempt solo without a local guide. The terrain is remote, trails are unmarked, and mobile signal is patchy. Guides are inexpensive and genuinely necessary here.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🥾 Horton Plains / World's End</h4>
      <p>Well-managed national park with rangers. One of the safest hikes for solo travellers — clear trails, entrance fees, regular visitors. Go early to beat clouds (arrive by 07:00).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>📶 Mobile signal</h4>
      <p>Dialog is the most reliable network in hill country and remote areas. Download offline maps (Maps.me or Google Maps offline) before you set off. Tell your guesthouse your planned route.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="safety-card">
      <h4>🏕 Rule of thumb</h4>
      <p>If a trail is popular, you can usually solo it safely in daylight hours with good preparation. If it's remote, unmarked, or in dense jungle — a guide is worth every rupee.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

